<b><u>Food Donations</u></b>
The BRICK accepts donations of nonperishable, unopened food items, and distributes food to program participants in Ashland and Bayfield counties. The following staples are always needed on the shelves:
<ul>
 	<li>Canned fruits and vegetables</li>
 	<li>Soup</li>
 	<li>Pasta and pasta sauce</li>
 	<li>Peanut butter</li>
 	<li>Cereal</li>
</ul>

<b><u>Personal Care Donations</u></b>
We accept personal care item donation.
The following are always accepted:
<ul>
 	<li>Bath soap</li>
 	<li>Shampoo</li>
 	<li>Toothpaste</li>
 	<li>Laundry soap</li>
 	<li>Diapers</li>
 	<li>Lotion</li>
 	<li>Toilet paper</li>
 	<li>Paper towels</li>
</ul>

<b><u>Collection Sites</u></b>
<ul>
 	<li><strong>Ashland
</strong>420 Ellis Ave. Ashland, WI 54806
(715)682-7425
Monday-Wednesday 9:00 am to 3:30 pm, Thursday 9:00 am to 7 pm
Closed Fridays</li>
 	<li><strong>Cable
</strong>Cable Area Food Shelf. 13380 Spruce St
Fourth Thursday Jan.-Oct., third Thursday Nov.-Dec., 11:00 am to 6:00 pm</li>
 	<li><strong>Cornucopia
</strong>South Shore Food Shelf, Town of Bell Community Center, County Highway C
Open the 1st and 3rd Thursday 10:00 am to 3:00 pm</li>
 	<li><strong>Mellen
</strong>The Brick’s Helping Hands Food Shelf,  Mellen City Hall (Lower level),  Main St
Third Thursday of every month 11:00 am to 6:00 pm</li>
</ul>
</span>
